The paper deals with the analysis of binary search trees (BSTs) and their performance on various types of sequences. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The use of forbidden-submatrix theory suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The study of dynamic optimality and access costs also relates to machine learning (cs.LG).
